glosses: to be burned, to catch fire

etymology: First sense is probably short cut of Ottoman Turkish كویندرمك (göyündürmek), from Old Anatolian Turkish كویندرمك (göyündürmek), from Proto-Turkic *köń-. The second sense is directly inherited through Ottoman Turkish and Old Anatolian Turkish كویمك (göymek). Cognate with Salar köydürgüsi (“to burn (tr.)”), Turkmen köýdürmek (“to burn (tr.)”).
